label: cor:accountingEntries
description: Root for XBRL GL. No entry made here.

label: cor:documentInfo
description: Parent for descriptive information about the accountingEntries section in which it is contained.

label: cor:entriesType
description: account: information to fill in a chart of accounts file.  balance: the results of accumulation of a complete and validated list of entries for an account   or a list of account in a specific period - sometimes called general ledger entries: a list of individual accounting entries, which might be posted/validated or nonposted/n  journal: a self-balancing   Dr = Cr list of entries for a specific period including beginning balance for that period.  ledger: a complete list of entries for a specific account   or list of accounts for a specific period; note - debits do not have to equal credits.  assets: a listing of open receivables, payables, inventory, fixed assets or other information that can be extracted from but are not necessarily included as part of a journal n  trialBalance: the self-balancing   Dr = Cr result of accumulation of a complete and validated list of entries for the entity in a complete list of accounts in a specific period. taxtables: aids automated interpretation of instances that represent tax tables; Tax table are defined by using multiple [taxes] structures to gather the population of codes, authorities and rates; through [taxTableCode] cross-references in the [taxes] structure, these "master file" tax tables can be referenced.   mapping: a collection of mappings between interrelated data sets, such as a local and related corporate standard chart of accounts or detail data mapped to summarized end reporting concepts.  versioning: a collection of changes between two versions of the same class of information, such as updates to a master file like a chart of accounts.   master_file: a collection of master files, such as the customer or inventory master file.   trade_documents: a collection of trade/transactional documents, such as vendor invoices or customer orders.   profile_compliant: the meaning of this collection of information can be determined by understanding an established profile and especially an XBRL GL Profile. Profiles are determined through namespace declarations, schemaRef and conventions of those profiles.  other: for all other types of representations.  Often sorted by date or by account, these terms have specific, and sometimes different, meanings in different areas. Common practice will drive accounting method/term matches.

label: cor:uniqueID
description: Unique identifier for this file.

label: cor:revisesUniqueID
description: Internal ID Number associated with identifierReference

label: cor:revisesUniqueIDAction
description: Provides guidance on action to take with previous set of data: supersedes - old data should be considered as obsolete/overwritten; supplements - belongs with that data as if it was included with it.

label: cor:language
description: Primary language of the intellectual content. Where practical, the content of this field should coincide with ISO 639-1988 language codes.

label: cor:creationDate
description: Date/time file was created.

label: bus:creator
description: Identifies the creator of the XBRL instance.

label: cor:entriesComment
description: Text for entire document.

label: cor:periodCoveredStart
description: Start of date range for contents. Used as basis for many assumptions about data, including the date as of which open balances are open.

label: cor:periodCoveredEnd
description: End of date range for contents. Used as basis for many assumptions about data, including the date as of which open balances are open.

label: bus:periodCount
description: Number of periods or buckets, used by postingCode. Used to interpret posting date. It may be preferable to limit entries by period covered to be by individual reporting period.

label: bus:periodUnit
description: Type of periods covered by periodCount. Enumerated as: daily, weekly, bi-weekly, semi-monthly, monthly, quarterly, thirdly, semiannual, annual, ad-hoc, current-period-only, other.

label: bus:periodUnitDescription
description: Free format description of the period unit

label: bus:sourceApplication
description: Product or service that produced this file. Used by many systems   e.g., VAT. Version number can be included or extended.

label: bus:targetApplication
description: Particular use for which file was generated.

label: muc:defaultCurrency
description: The default currency related to the amount can be entered here instead of the XBRL instance specified way, especially important in multi-currency situations. Recommend ISO 4217 coding

label: cor:entityInformation
description: Holder for entity information - information about the reporting organization.

label: bus:entityPhoneNumber
description: Primary phone number of the entity.

label: bus:phoneNumberDescription
description: Entity Phone Number Description such as Main, Investor relations. Enumerated as: bookkeeper, controller, direct, fax, investor-relations, main, switchboard, other.

label: bus:phoneNumber
description: Phone number referred to in 'phoneNumberDescription'

label: bus:entityFaxNumberStructure
description: Tuple for holding company fax information.

label: bus:entityFaxNumberUsage
description: Company fax number usage   e.g. orders, head office, IR

label: bus:entityFaxNumber
description: Company Fax Number

label: bus:entityEmailAddressStructure
description: Tuple for holding company email information.

label: bus:entityEmailAddressUsage
description: Company email address usage   e.g. orders, head office, IR

label: bus:entityEmailAddress
description: Company Email Address

label: bus:organizationAccountingMethodPurposeDefault
description: If not stated explicitly at the line level, the default reporting purpose - from book, tax, management, statutory, other

label: bus:organizationAccountingMethodPurposeDefaultDescription
description: Free format description of the default accounting method purpose

label: bus:organizationIdentifiers
description: Section which contains various identifiers for the company.

label: bus:organizationIdentifier
description: Code representing the company or organization whose data this file represents: used for situations where one user   e.g., a CPA needs to keep track of multiple organizations' files   e.g., multiple clients. Can be EIN#, client #, internal/external identifier, SIC code. Codes which identifies the entity. Includes the code identifier of the authority issuing the code, a colon, and the code itself. For example, CIK:01234567 for the CIK number issued by SEC EDGAR.

label: bus:organizationDescription
description: Text for organization identified by organizationIdentifier. Any descriptive information about the code.

label: bus:organizationAddress
description: Address structure for the reporting entity

label: bus:organizationAddressName
description: Name of organization used at this address

label: bus:organizationAddressDescription
description: Description of the address, such as Mailing, Physical, Investor Relations, etc.

label: bus:organizationAddressPurpose
description: Freeform for codes like shipping, billing, mailing at address level.  Allows identification of multiple purpose addresses for each address of the reporting organization.

label: bus:organizationAddressLocationIdentifier
description: A code used to identify the location and to associate it with contacts and transactions

label: bus:organizationBuildingNumber
description: Building Number

label: bus:organizationAddressStreet
description: Street address

label: bus:organizationAddressStreet2
description: Address Detail

label: bus:organizationAddressCity
description: City or town of the address.

label: bus:organizationAddressStateOrProvince
description: State, province or region of the address.

label: bus:organizationAddressZipOrPostalCode
description: Zip or other postal code of the address.

label: bus:organizationAddressCountry
description: Country of the address.

label: bus:organizationAddressActive
description: Boolean to indicate whether the address is active   ="true" or inactive   ="false"

label: bus:entityWebSite
description: Primary web site of the entity.

label: bus:webSiteDescription
description: Description of the web site.

label: bus:webSiteURL
description: Valid URL of the web site. Should be full URL.

label: bus:contactInformation
description: Information about contacts.

label: bus:contactPrefix
description: Prefix   e.g. Dr., Mr., Mrs.

label: bus:contactLastName
description: Last or family name

label: bus:contactFirstName
description: First or given name

label: bus:contactSuffix
description: Suffix   e.g. MD, CPA, Jr.

label: bus:contactAttentionLine
description: Attention Line

label: bus:contactPositionRole
description: Position or role

label: bus:contactPhone
description: Contact Phone Number

label: bus:contactPhoneNumberDescription
description: Contact Phone Number Description such as Main, Investor relations, etc. Enumerated as: bookkeeper, controller, direct, fax, investor-relations, main, switchboard, other.

label: bus:contactPhoneNumber
description: Contact phone number referred to in the description.

label: bus:contactFax
description: Contact Fax Number Structure

label: bus:contactFaxNumberUsage
description: Contact Fax Number Usage   e.g. orders, head office, IR

label: bus:contactFaxNumber
description: Contact Fax Number

label: bus:contactEMail
description: Contact E-mail address structure

label: bus:contactEmailAddressUsage
description: Contact email address usage   e.g. orders, head office, IR

label: bus:contactEmailAddress
description: Contact email address

label: bus:contactType
description: Role of contact. Examples include: Source Service, Sender, Recipient, Invoicer, Auditor, Accountant

label: bus:contactLocationIdentifierCrossReference
description: This code is used to associate the contact with a specific location for the Entity. Its value should be the same as that of the organizationAddressLocationIdentifier

label: bus:contactActive
description: Boolean to indicate whether the contact is active   ="true" or inactive   ="false"

label: bus:businessDescription
description: Description of the nature of the business of the entity.

label: bus:fiscalYearStart
description: Start of fiscal year. Where appropriate, corporate year period representation permits non-365 or 366 day years   more appropriate for internal sharing than data from external sources In Europe, some jurisdictions allow 2 year minus 1 day fiscal years.

label: bus:fiscalYearEnd
description: End of fiscal year. Where appropriate, corporate year period representation permits non-365 or 366 day years   more appropriate for internal sharing than data from external sources In Europe, some jurisdictions allow 2 year minus 1 day fiscal years.

label: bus:organizationAccountingMethodStructure
description: Section for identifying the methods of accounting used by the entity for different reporting purposes

label: bus:organizationAccountingMethod
description: For this entity, the method of accounting represented - from: accrual, cash, modified cash, modified accrual, encumbrance, special methods, hybrid methods, other

label: bus:organizationAccountingMethodDescription
description: Free format description of the accounting method

label: bus:organizationAccountingMethodPurpose
description: For this entity, the reporting purpose represented - from book, tax, management, statutory, other

label: bus:organizationAccountingMethodPurposeDescription
description: Free format description of the accounting method purpose

label: bus:organizationAccountingMethodStartDate
description: Accounting Method Start Date

label: bus:organizationAccountingMethodEndDate
description: Accounting Method End Date

label: bus:accountantInformation
description: Information about the relevant external accountant

label: bus:accountantName
description: Name of the accountant

label: bus:accountantAddress

label: bus:accountantAddressDescription
description: Address Description for Accountant

label: bus:accountantAddressPurpose
description: Address Purpose

label: bus:accountantAddressLocationIdentifier
description: A code used to identify the accountant location and to associate it with contacts and transactions

label: bus:accountantBuildingNumber
description: Building Number for Accountant

label: bus:accountantStreet
description: Street address of the accountant

label: bus:accountantZipOrPostalCode

description: Free format description of the type of engagement

description: Accountant contact E-mail address structure

description: Accountant Contact email address usage   e.g. orders, head office, IR

description: Accountant Contact email address

label: bus:reportingCalendar
description: A tool to collect the periods used to summarise results from transactions.

label: bus:reportingCalendarCode
description: The code used to identify this specific reporting calendar, unique across periods

label: bus:reportingCalendarDescription
description: A description of the reporting calendar   associated with the reportingCalendarCode given

label: bus:reportingCalendarTitle
description: A description of the reporting period. The actual beginning and ending dates are found within the 'reportingCalendarPeriod' structure

label: bus:reportingCalendarPeriod
description: A tool to collect a specific set of periods used to summarize results from transactions.

label: bus:reportingCalendarPeriodTypeDescription
description: A description of the type of period involved.

label: bus:reportingCalendarOpenClosedStatus
description: An identifier on whether the reporting calendar is still open for activity. enumerated, "open", "closed", "pending"

label: bus:reportingPurpose
description: A description of the accounting set of books involved. Uses enumeration from accounting method purpose.

label: bus:reportingPurposeDescription
description: Free format description of the reporting purpose

label: bus:reportingCalendarPeriodType
description: A code for the type of period involved. Enumerated as: monthly, quarterly, semi-annually, 4-5-4, ad-hoc, other.

label: bus:periodIdentifier
description: An identifier for this period in this calendar

label: bus:periodDescription
description: A description of this specific reporting period in this calendar.

label: bus:periodStart
description: The beginning date/time of a period

label: bus:periodEnd
description: The ending date/time of a period

label: bus:periodClosedDate
description: The date/time a period has been closed for activity. If this is present with a nill value   xsi:nill="true" then the period is not closed.

label: cor:entryHeader
description: Parent for entry headers/journal entry headers.

label: cor:postedDate
description: Date this entry was posted   validated to the general ledger. May not represent the date of accounting significance which is represented by 'postingDate'.

label: cor:enteredBy
description: Initials/name of operator originally entering.

label: bus:enteredByModified
description: Identification for the last person modifying this entry before posting.

label: cor:enteredDate
description: Represents the actual date/time of entry into computer   automated from system date, often misrepresented by changing system clock. Posting dates are maintained separately.

label: bus:entryResponsiblePerson
description: Identifier of person who created or originated or is otherwise responsible for the entry.

label: cor:sourceJournalID
description: Source journal. The code of the journal in which the entry is processed.  The code must be a unique indication for a journal and is selected from the following enumerated list:  cd      cash disbursements   sending cheques to vendors cr      cash receipts   receiving cheques from others fa      fixed assets  gi      giro/other bank adjustments gj      general journal im      inventory management  jc      job cost  pj      purchase journal  liabilities from purchases  pl      payroll journal sj      sales journal se      standard entries  ud      user defined  ot      other sources of entries

label: bus:sourceJournalDescription
description: Source journal   full description of general journal, payroll journal, accountant entries. A more easily readable journal indication. The most common journals are: Purchases, Sales, Cash, and General Journal.

label: cor:entryType
description: One of the following enumerated list: adjusting, budget, comparative, external-accountant, standard, passed-adjusting, eliminating, proposed, recurring, reclassifying, simulated, tax, other

label: bus:entryOrigin
description: Origin of entry: accrual, manual entry, imported entry, exchange gain or loss

label: cor:entryNumber
description: Identifier within source journal

label: cor:entryComment
description: Description of entry described by this entry header   e.g. Opening Balance

label: cor:qualifierEntry
description: Entry Qualifier - An enumerated field that qualifies the type of entry, specifically useful for general ledger and trial balance environments when it is important to state the values represented are summarized as of the reporting date - opening or closing balances. In accounting systems, this is often known as BBF   balance brought forward. Permitted values are: standard, balance-brought-forward and other.

label: cor:qualifierEntryDescription
description: Free format description of the entry qualifier

label: bus:postingCode
description: Code for posting to period, e.g., period 1-13, based on codes in an accounting period file. We do not recommend that software vendors export here, but suggest providing period end numbers for the buckets. Possibilities W1 through W53, M1 through M13, Q1-Q4. Developers and others creating output files are encouraged to supply an actual end date.

label: bus:batchID
description: ID for a batch for this group of entries

label: bus:batchDescription
description: Description of this batch

label: bus:numberOfEntries
description: The total number of entries.

label: bus:totalDebit
description: The total of all debit amounts.

label: bus:totalCredit
description: The total of all credit amounts.

label: cor:bookTaxDifference
description: Enumerated field with possible values of permanent, temporary or none indicating the type of difference between book and tax accounting methods. Omission of this field is equivalent to "none"

label: bus:eliminationCode
description: Informs destination ledger this is an intracompany entry which eliminates in consolidation

label: bus:budgetScenarioPeriodStart
description: Start of period covered by associated budgetScenario

label: bus:budgetScenarioPeriodEnd
description: End of period covered by associated budgetScenario

label: bus:budgetScenarioText
description: Text related to budgetScenario

label: bus:budgetScenario
description: Code for a budget scenario identifier   such as PB for 'preliminary budget', or RB for 'revised budget', or other identifier for entryType

label: bus:budgetAllocationCode
description: Code associated with the calculation formula: e.g.   Divide by number of periods,   Total for period given

label: usk:reversingStdId
description: For standard, reversing, master, cancelling or other entries an ID associated with those entries.

label: usk:recurringStdDescription
description: Description to accompany standard or recurring ID

label: usk:frequencyInterval
description: For standard or recurring journals, how often entry may be made: every frequencyInterval frequencyUnit, such as every 7   interval days   unit or every 1   interval quarter   unit. This field represents the interval.

label: usk:frequencyUnit
description: For standard or recurring journals, how often entry may be made: every frequencyInterval frequencyUnit, such as every 7   interval days   unit or every 1   interval quarter   unit. This field represents the unit.

label: usk:repetitionsRemaining
description: Number of times that the recurring entry will repeat

label: usk:nextDateRepeat
description: Date next repeated or standard posted

label: usk:lastDateRepeat
description: Date last repeated or standard posted

label: usk:endDateRepeatingEntry
description: For standard or recurring journals, stop date/time for repetitive entry.

label: usk:reverse
description: Should entry be reversed?

label: usk:reversingDate
description: Date this entry should be reversed

label: cor:entryNumberCounter
description: Unique reference for the entry - a numeric counter

label: cor:entryDetail
description: Parent for entry detail

label: cor:lineNumber
description: Identifier for a particular entry detail

label: cor:lineNumberCounter
description: Unique reference for the line - a numeric counter

label: cor:account
description: Tuple: parent container for account numbers and identifiers. No entry is made here, but each detail line may have multiple accounts assigned to it for reporting in different GAAPs, offsetting accounts in Japan, passing along information to consolidation systems about local versus consolidating accounts, etc. For example, the account 4783HG-QOWI-192837-1000 may be expressed so: /account/accountMainID 1000 /account/accountMainDescription Cash  /account/accountSub/accountSubID 4783HG /account/accountSub/accountSubDescription Department  /account/accountSub/accountSubID QOWI /account/accountSub/accountSubDescription Branch  /account/accountSub/accountSubID 192837 /account/accountSub/accountSubDescription Division

label: cor:accountMainID
description: Main account - the code used to identify the accounting bucket the entry has been assigned to. Examples might be 1000 for Cash, 567GAAZ for Sales Expense or Z for tax payments. Identifiers such as department, branch, division, manager, or other modifiers are noted in the Subaccount area. Before needing to post, account is not necessary. Posting to the general ledger almost always requires an entry here.

label: cor:accountMainDescription
description: Description of accountMainID - the human readable describer that accompanies the code used in accountMainID

label: cor:mainAccountType
description: Account type - FASB Concepts 6 and similar international designs. When xbrlInfo is used to associated other XBRL reporting items, this field is more suited to representing existing systems   audit than data interchange. Enumerated as: asset, liability, equity, income, gain, expense, loss, contr-to-equity, distr-from-equity, comprehensive-income, other.

label: cor:mainAccountTypeDescription
description: Free format description of the account classification

label: cor:parentAccountMainID
description: Roll up item from child natural account to parent natural account.

label: cor:accountPurposeCode
description: Code related to usage for account aggregate - Consolidating, European, IFRS, Offsetting, Primary, Tax, USGAAP, Japanese, Other. Japanese companies will use this for the tax required offsetting entry. If left blank, assumes default accounting method for company.

label: cor:accountPurposeDescription
description: Description of usage for aggregate account

label: cor:accountType
description: Type of account. Enumerated as: account, bank, employee, customer, job, vendor, measurable, statistical, other.

label: cor:accountTypeDescription
description: Free format description of the account type

label: bus:entryAccountingMethod
description: For this entry, the method of accounting represented - from: accrual, cash, modified cash, modified accrual, encumbrance, special methods, hybrid methods, other

label: bus:entryAccountingMethodDescription
description: Free format description of the entry accounting method

label: bus:entryAccountingMethodPurpose
description: For this entry, the reporting purpose represented - from book, tax, management, statutory, other

label: bus:entryAccountingMethodPurposeDescription
description: Free format description of the entry accounting method purpose

label: cor:accountSub
description: Tuple to hold multiple accountSubIDs and Descriptions

label: cor:accountSubDescription
description: The description that accompanies accountSubID belongs here.

label: cor:accountSubID
description: Where the primary account was placed in accountMainID, the code used for each profit center, division, business unit, fund, program, branch, project, class, su-class or other modifier is placed here.

label: cor:accountSubType
description: Type of sub-account - profit center, division, business unit, fund, program, branch, project, class, su-class or other modifier is placed here. For example: Accountability center: Business unit: Class:Department: Project: Fund: Program:Job: Profit center: Branch: Setup class: Division: Unit

label: cor:segmentParentTuple
description: Tuple for showing the detail necessary to roll up from one segment   type of subaccount to another.

label: cor:parentSubaccountCode
description: Subaccount NUMBER this subaccount rolls up to - see also subaccount type it rolls up to.

label: cor:parentSubaccountType
description: The describer of the segment this subaccount rolls up to.

label: cor:reportingTreeIdentifier
description: Used for representing descriptions of reporting trees.

label: cor:parentSubaccountProportion
description: For partial allocations of amounts to different parents, the percentage of a child that will be allocated to a parent.

label: cor:accountActive
description: Boolean to indicate whether the account is active   ="true" or inactive   ="false"

label: cor:amount
description: This field   amount represents the primary monetary amount related to the  subject of the entryDetail line.  There is one primary monetary amount per entryDetail structure. It may, for example, represent the amount of one line of a journal entry, the balance on a document, or the extended amount of a line item on an invoice.   Amount is not required if detailed entry is used for non-financial work and other elements are populated, in particular measurableQuantity.   The amount field is a signed number   either positive or negative itself and used in conjunction with a separate signOfAmount and a separate debitCreditCode, which together are considered for understanding the monetary amount.  The unit of measure is determined by amountCurrency if present, and by the default or home currency if amountCurrency is not present.

label: muc:amountCurrency
description: The currency related to the amount can be entered here instead of the XBRL instance specified way, especially important in multi-currency situations.   Recommend ISO 4217 coding.

label: muc:amountOriginalAmount
description: Amount in original   as opposed to home currency, for multi-currency tracking.

label: muc:amountOriginalCurrency
description: The currency used to track original, as opposed to home, amounts. Recommended ISO 4217 coding.

label: muc:amountOriginalExchangeRate
description: Exchange rate at time of original transaction   expressed as national currency divided by original currency

label: muc:amountOriginalExchangeRateDate
description: Date of exchange rate used to record the original transaction.

label: muc:amountOriginalExchangeRateSource
description: Source of Exchange Rate - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

label: muc:amountOriginalExchangeRateComment
description: Comment about exchange rate used for recording original transaction.

label: muc:amountOriginalTriangulationAmount
description: If triangulation is used, amount in triangulation currency, for multi-currency tracking. Debit is entered as positive, credit as negative.

label: muc:amountOriginalTriangulationCurrency
description: The currency used for triangulation, if used. May often be EUR or USD. Recommended ISO 4217 coding.

label: muc:amountOriginalTriangulationExchangeRate
description: Exchange rate between national currency and triangulation currency at time of original transaction   expressed as national currency divided by triangulation currency

label: muc:amountOriginalTriangulationExchangeRateSource
description: Source of Exchange Rate for triangulation amount at time of original transaction - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

label: muc:amountOriginalTriangulationExchangeRateType
description: Type of Exchange Rate for triangulation amount at time of original transaction - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

label: muc:originalTriangulationExchangeRate
description: Exchange rate between original currency and triangulation currency at time of original transaction   expressed as original currency divided by triangulation currency

label: muc:originalExchangeRateTriangulationSource
description: Source of Exchange Rate for triangulation from original currency to triangulation currency at time of original transaction - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

label: muc:originalExchangeRateTriangulationType
description: Type of Exchange Rate for triangulation from original currency to triangulation currency at time of original transaction - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

label: cor:signOfAmount
description: Sign of amount; provides 4 possible fields only when used in conjunction with debitCreditCode; primarily used for correcting entries so total debits and credits after an entry error are not inflated. D + increase DebitsD - decrease debitsC + decreases creditC - increases credit

label: cor:debitCreditCode
description: Optional identifier of whether the amount is a   Debit, a   Credit or Undefined

label: cor:postingDate
description: At the detail level, this represents the accounting significance date. No matter what date the document is received, entered, or posted, this signifies the accounting date of the entry. If you want to see the financial results for March 5, 2002 and this entry is given that date, the entry will be part of the results for March 5, 2002. This is different from the postedDate found at the entryHeader level. If you want the accounting significance to be a particular date, it goes here. A single entry could represent multiple dates, but would only be posted on one date.

label: bus:amountMemo
description: A boolean like entry that indicates whether an entryDetail line has been provided solely to provide additional details and that tools should not consider the amount in postings.

label: bus:allocationCode
description: A code that is tied to the Enterprise's allocation system.

label: muc:multicurrencyDetail
description: Section to provide additional information related to home currencies that differ from original currencies and related exchange rates - typically this will be used to record exchange rates and amounts in currencies and/or on dates other than those of the original transaction. This structure allows recording of exchange rates using a third currency as a triangulation currency. This is often EUR but is not restricted to being so. This structure may be repeated as many times as necessary to record amounts in foreign currencies on the same or different dates.

label: muc:multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate
description: Date of exchange rate   other than original transaction date on which amount is expressed as amountRestatedAmount or amountTriangulationAmount

label: muc:amountRestatedAmount
description: The amount in the foreign currency identified by amountRestatedCurrency as of multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate.

label: muc:amountRestatedCurrency
description: The currency in which amountRestatedAmount is expressed. Recommended ISO 4217 coding.

label: muc:amountRestatedExchangeRate
description: Exchange rate used to convert amountRestatedAmount as of multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate   expressed as national currency divided by foreign currency

label: muc:amountRestatedExchangeRateSource
description: Source of Exchange Rate for restated amount - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

label: muc:amountRestatedExchangeRateType
description: Type of Exchange Rate for restated amount - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

label: muc:amountTriangulationAmount
description: The amount in the triangulation currency identified by amountTriangulationCurrency as of multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate.

label: muc:amountTriangulationCurrency
description: The currency used for tringulation between amountRestatedCurrency and the home currency. Recommended ISO 4217 coding.

label: muc:amountTriangulationExchangeRate
description: Exchange rate used to convert amountTriangulationAmount as of multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate   expressed as national currency divided by triangulation currency

label: muc:amountTriangulationExchangeRateSource
description: Source of Exchange Rate for triangulation amount - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

label: muc:amountTriangulationExchangeRateType
description: Type of Exchange Rate for triangulation amount - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

label: muc:restatedTriangulationExchangeRate
description: Exchange rate used to convert from amountRestatedAmount to amountTriangulationAmount as of multicurrencyDetailExchangeRateDate   expressed as foreign currency divided by triangulation currency

label: muc:restatedExchangeRateTriangulationSource
description: Source of Exchange Rate for converting between foreign currency and triangulation currency - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

label: muc:restatedExchangeRateTriangulationType
description: Type of Exchange Rate for converting between foreign currency and triangulation currency - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

label: muc:multicurrencyDetailComment
description: Comment describing the enclosing multicurrencyDetail tuple's contents. May include reason for recording additional exchange rates other than that used at the time of the original transaction.

label: cor:identifierReference
description: Identification for customer, vendor, or employee.

label: cor:identifierCode
description: N/A

label: cor:identifierExternalReference
description: Structure containing references to an external authority associated with identifier

label: cor:identifierAuthorityCode
description: External Authority   e,g, Tax Authority ID Number associated with identifierReference

label: cor:identifierAuthority
description: Name of External Authority   e.g. Tax Authority

label: cor:identifierAuthorityVerificationDate
description: Date on which the External Authority last performed a verification

label: cor:identifierOrganizationType
description: Identifier Organization Type. Enumerated as: individual, organization, other.

label: cor:identifierOrganizationTypeDescription
description: Free format description of the identifier organization type

label: cor:identifierDescription
description: Textual description of identifierReference.

label: cor:identifierType
description: Entity type   enumerated: C, customer, E, employee, V, vendor, O, other, I, salesperson-internal, X, salesperson-external, N, contractor.

label: cor:identifierCategory
description: For use as Customer, Vendor or Employee Class   such as Residential/Commercial/Institutional/Government or Retail/Wholesale or other classifications used by business.

label: cor:identifierEMail
description: Email address for Identifier.

label: cor:identifierEmailAddressUsage
description: Identifer Email Address Usage   e.g. Orders, Head Office, IR

label: cor:identifierEmailAddress
description: Identifer Email Address

label: cor:identifierPhoneNumber
description: Phone number related to Identifier.

label: cor:identifierPhoneNumberDescription
description: Identifier Phone Number Usage   e.g. Main, Investor relations, etc.. Enumerated as: bookkeeper, controller, direct, fax, investor-relations, main, switchboard, other.

label: cor:identifierPhone
description: Identifier Phone Number

label: cor:identifierFaxNumber
description: Fax number structure related to identifier.

label: cor:identifierFaxNumberUsage
description: Identifer Fax Number Usage   e.g. Orders, Head Office, IR

label: cor:identifierFax
description: Identifer Fax Number

label: bus:identifierPurpose
description: Freeform for codes like purchasing, billing, manufacturing at identifier level.

label: bus:identifierAddress
description: Address   block of customer, vendor, employee for integration purposes, VAT.

label: bus:identifierAddressDescription
description: For use when the addressee identifier for this address is different than the primary description of the identified party.

label: bus:identifierAddressPurpose
description: Freeform for codes like shipping, billing, mailing at address level.  Allows identification of multiple purpose addresses for each identifier.

label: bus:identifierBuildingNumber
description: Building Number for Identifier Address

label: bus:identifierStreet
description: Street address.

label: bus:identifierAddressStreet2
description: Address Detail for Identifier Address

label: bus:identifierCity
description: City

label: bus:identifierStateOrProvince
description: State or province

label: bus:identifierCountry
description: Country

label: bus:identifierZipOrPostalCode
description: Zip or other postal code

label: bus:identifierAddressLocationIdentifier
description: A code used to identify the identifier location and to associate it with contacts

label: cor:identifierContactInformationStructure
description: Identifier Contact Information Structure

label: cor:identifierContactPrefix
description: Prefix   e.g. Dr., Mr., Mrs.

label: cor:identifierContactLastName
description: Identifier Contact Last or Family Name

label: cor:identifierContactFirstName
description: First or given name

label: cor:identifierContactSuffix
description: Suffix   e.g. MD, CPA, Jr.

label: cor:identifierContactAttentionLine
description: Attention Line

label: cor:identifierContactPositionRole
description: Position or Role

label: cor:identifierContactPhone
description: Phone Number

label: cor:identifierContactPhoneNumberDescription
description: Identifier Contact Phone Number Usage   Main, Investor Relations, etc.. Enumerated as: bookkeeper, controller, direct, fax, investor-relations, main, switchboard, other.

label: cor:identifierContactPhoneNumber
description: Identifier Contact Phone Number

label: cor:identifierContactFax
description: Fax Number

label: cor:identifierContactFaxNumberUsage
description: Identifer Contact Fax Number Usage   e.g. Orders, Head Office, IR

label: cor:identifierContactFaxNumber
description: Identifer Contact Fax Number

label: cor:identifierContactEmail
description: Email Address

label: cor:identifierContactEmailAddressUsage
description: Identifer Contact Email Address Usage   e.g. Orders, Head Office, IR

label: cor:identifierContactEmailAddress
description: Identifer Contact Email Address

label: cor:identifierContactType
description: Identifier Contact Type

label: bus:identifierLocationIdentifierCrossReference
description: This code is used to associate the contact with a specific location for the Identifier. Its value should be the same as that of the identifierAddressLocationIdentifier

label: cor:identifierActive
description: Boolean to indicate whether the identifier is active   ="true" or inactive   ="false"

label: cor:documentType
description: An enumerated field describing the original source document, with check, debit-memo, credit-memo, finance-charge, invoice, order-customer, order-vendor, payment-other, reminder, tegata, voucher, shipment, receipt, manual-adjustment, other.

label: cor:documentTypeDescription
description: Free format description of the document type

label: cor:invoiceType
description: Invoice Type    self-billed, ePoS enumerated values

label: cor:documentNumber
description: Invoice, check, voucher, or other source document identifier

label: cor:documentApplyToNumber
description: Document number of primary invoice number, used to offset payments, debits and credits; for an invoice, usually the same as the documentNumber. When calculating open balance on an invoice, or open amount on payments in advance or not fully applied, this permits calculation of the open item.

label: cor:documentReference
description: Internal reference for the document above; number assigned internally to track the document

label: cor:documentDate
description: Date   and less likely in the paper world but possible in the e-world, time on actual document   invoice, voucher, check date. Other dates control posting information.

label: bus:documentReceivedDate
description: Date/time document was noted as received   if necessary. Represents actual date received. Posting dates are maintained separately.

label: bus:documentChargeReimb
description: Is this entry chargeable to client, reimbursable? Used by some systems to indicate that account on posting/validation should be posted to a customer or vendor's account.

label: bus:documentLocation
description: Document location as URI, file name or other reference. Alternatively, text of document can be placed here.

label: bus:paymentMethod
description: Method used or to be used to make the payment

label: cor:postingStatus
description: deferred: although entered, it cannot be posted until a later time  posted: already posted  proposed: a proposed item that must be approved simulated: a simulated item, for what-if  tax: a tax-specific entry unposted:entered but not yet posted or validated  cancelled:entered and later cancelled other:other status - should be described in postingStatusDescription

label: cor:postingStatusDescription
description: Free format description of the posting status

label: cor:detailComment
description: Description of this line of detail only

label: cor:dateAcknowledged
description: Date of acknowledgement of goods/services shipped/received.

label: cor:confirmedDate
description: Date of confirmation of shipment/receipt.

label: cor:shipFrom
description: References organizationAddressLocationIdentifier where used. Otherwise freeform.

label: cor:shipReceivedDate
description: Date goods/services are shipped/received.

label: cor:maturityDate
description: Due date or other maturity date.

label: cor:terms
description: Discount/payment terms.

label: bus:measurable
description: Parent for information regarding measurable items associated with the enclosing entryDetail line. Primary area used for holding performance measures. Based on needs for tracking inventory transactional detail, but suitable for anything assigned to an "account", "reporting bucket" or "code". Can be used to track any movements.

label: bus:measurableCode
description: Code for measurable item including BP - Business process, FA - Fixed asset/Capitalized item, IN - Inventory, KPI - Metric, NT - Intangible, SP - Supplies, SV-P - Service by employee, vendor or contractor, SV-M - Service by equipment/machinery, OT - Other

label: bus:measurableCodeDescription
description: Free format description of the measurable code

label: bus:measurableCategory
description: Category of the measurable

label: bus:measurableID
description: Internal inventory part or SKU number or other code identifier for the measurable.

label: bus:measurableIDSchema
description: URI or other identifier for schema with which measurable ID can be validated

label: bus:measurableIDOther
description: Second identifier   such as vendor's item number

label: bus:measurableIDOtherSchema
description: URI or other identifier for schema with which measurable ID Other can be validated

label: bus:measurableDescription
description: Text description of measurable   e.g. inventory item or other identifier

label: bus:measurableQuantity
description: Number of units in this transaction; for non-monetary calculations; can be square footage, number of people, etc.

label: bus:measurableQualifier
description: Field that can represent grading, inspection codes, ratings and other qualifiers to properly capture PKI/Balanced Scorecard information

label: bus:measurableUnitOfMeasure
description: Description of unit: e.g. each, case, dozen, etc. ISO standard coding recommended.

label: bus:measurableCostPerUnit
description: Per unit price of the measurable. Although one might expect that measurableQuantity * measurableCostPerUnit = amount, this is not mandated except by external rules sets.

label: bus:measurableStartDateTime
description: Start time of the duration being measured

label: bus:measurableEndDateTime
description: End time of the duration being measured

label: bus:measurableActive
description: Boolean to indicate whether the measurable is active   ="true" or inactive   ="false"

label: bus:jobInfo
description: Tuple for holding job related information, separate from jobs represented in account identifier. Would probably only have one jobinfo tuple for each entry line, but there may be a need to express more than one.

label: usk:jobCode
description: Associated job number or code. This could be built into the account, but many systems maintain a separate job coding system. Use primarily if job identification is a separate system, and not considered part of the chart of accounts.

label: usk:jobDescription
description: Description of job

label: usk:jobPhaseCode
description: Job code, phase, activity. Allows greater granularity than a simple job number. Although the core only reaches down from job to phases, this can be customized to extend down to cost codes.

label: usk:jobPhaseDescription
description: Description of Job code, phase, activity

label: usk:jobActive
description: Boolean to indicate whether the job is active   ="true" or inactive   ="false"

label: bus:depreciationMortgage
description: Parent for information related to depreciation, mortgages, etc.

label: bus:dmJurisdiction
description: Jurisdiction   e.g. federal, state, local: e.g. US Federal, Province of Qubec, other identifier. Enumerated as: F, federal, S, state, L, local, other.

label: bus:dmMethodType
description: Type of depreciation method: used for information about the loan percentage for loan or the depreciation method. This is used for informational purposes only. Examples of entries are "20%", "5 year DDB"   Double Declining Balance.

label: bus:dmLifeLength
description: Length of life in number of periods.

label: bus:dmComment
description: Description of each item related to depreciation, mortgage, loan, credit facility, etc.

label: bus:dmStartDate
description: Start of the applicable period of each item related to depreciation, mortgage, loan, credit facility, etc.

label: bus:dmEndDate
description: End of the applicable period of each item related to depreciation, mortgage, loan, credit facility, etc.

label: bus:dmAmount
description: Amount of a cost or fee charged for a mortgage, loan, credit facility, etc.

label: ehm:measurableClassID
description: An enumerated code to identify the inventory, fixed asset or other measurable class. Enumerated as: raw material, work-in-process, finished goods, assemblies, supplies, land, building, machinery, furniture, vehicles, other.

label: ehm:measurableClassDescription
description: Free format description associated with gl-ehm:measurableClassID to provide specialization or clarification for the enumerated value of other.

label: ehm:costingMethodCode
description: An enumerated code for the inventory   or other measurable costing method. Enumerated as: LIFO, FIFO, average, weighted-average, standard-cost, tax-basis, book-basis, other.

label: ehm:costingMethodDescription
description: Free format description associated with gl-ehm:costingMethodCode to provide specialization of clarification for the enumerated value of other.

label: ehm:geospatialCoordinate
description: Enter a relevant location for this item. Format can be either: - Degrees, minutes, and seconds   DMS: 4124'12.2 N 210'26.5 E - Degrees and decimal minutes   DMM: 41 24.2028, 2 10.4418  - Decimal degrees   DD: 41.40338, 2.17403

label: ehm:serialLot
description: Tuple for holding information about serial numbers or lots   batches. As a tuple, this permits multiple serial numbers or multiple lot number batches within a single gl-cor:measurable structure.

label: ehm:serialLotCode
description: Is this item tracked by serial numbers or lot numbers? A serial number is usually a unique number assigned to a single; a lot or batch number is provided when a batch of items is fungible but must be differentiated from similar items from other batches. Enumerated indicator for serial or lot items. Enumeration are: serial, lot, other, neither. If not included within the tuple, neither is assumed.

label: ehm:serialLotDescription
description: Free format description associated with gl-ehm:serialLotCode to provide specialization and especially to provide clarification for the enumerated value of other in serialLotCode. Examples might be batch or group.

label: ehm:serialLotNumber
description: The holder for that actual serial number or lot   batch number/code assigned to an item or a batch of items.

label: ehm:nextSerialLotNumber
description: A field for holding the next expected serial or lot number to be given to future assignments, or for chaining between already assigned items.

label: ehm:serialLotQuantity
description: The quantity of units in this particular batch. Unit of measure is the gl-bus:measurableUnitofMeasure.

label: ehm:serialLotOriginalQuantity
description: The quantity of units in this batch on inception.

label: ehm:serialLotRemainingQuantity
description: The remaining quantity of units from the original batch; may be the same as the quantity in this batch or include other batches from the same original batch.

label: ehm:serialLotOrigination
description: Date of manufacture or creation.

label: ehm:serialLotExpiration
description: Expiration date of the batch.

label: ehm:serialLotManufacturer
description: Manufacturer of the item   serial or items   lot/batch.

label: ehm:serialLotBatchDescription
description: A name or description of the items in the lot or batch.

label: ehm:serialLotWarrantyStartDate
description: If the items are covered by warranty, when that warranty covered will begin or has begun.

label: ehm:serialLotWarrantyEndDate
description: If the items are covered by warranty, when that warranty covered will end or ended.

label: ehm:serialLotWarrantyPeriod
description: Warranty period  numeric portion; for a 30 day warranty period, the 30 would go here, and the day would go in gl-ehm:serialLotWarrantyPeriodUnit.

label: ehm:serialLotWarrantyPeriodUnit
description: Warrant period  time or cycle unit portion. Values from the XBRL Unit Registry   www.xbrl.org/utr/utr.xml are suggested where possible. Examples might include: H   hours D   days M   months Y   years machine cycles, km   kilometers.

label: ehm:serialLotWarrantyVendor
description: The vendor providing warranty; this may differ from the manufacturer.

label: ehm:serialLotWarrantyContract
description: Contract or document information related to the warranty, such as a contract number and date or a URL with more information.

label: ehm:serialLotComment
description: Free format text related to the serial number or lot.

label: cor:taxes
description: Tuple for holding tax related information

label: cor:taxAuthority
description: Name of the relevant tax authority

label: cor:taxTableCode
description: Tax table code used by the relevant tax authority

label: cor:taxDescription
description: Description of tax authority

label: cor:taxAmount
description: Amount of taxes

label: cor:taxBasis
description: Basis for taxation

label: cor:taxPercentageRate
description: Percent rate for VAT or other taxes normally a number between 0 and 1.0 - e.g. 50% is represented as 0.5

label: cor:taxCode
description: A class or category of taxes

label: cor:taxCommentExemption
description: Additional text/code for exemption reasons or other comments.

label: muc:taxAmountForeignCurrency
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency, the amount of tax in that currency

label: muc:taxCurrency
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency, that currency

label: muc:taxExchangeRateDate
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency, the date or date and time of the exchange rate used

label: muc:taxExchangeRate
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency, the exchange rate used expressed as national currency divided by foreign currency

label: muc:taxExchangeRateSource
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency, source of exchange rate - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

label: muc:taxExchangeRateType
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency, type of exchange rate - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

label: muc:taxExchangeRateComment
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency, comment about exchange rate used

label: muc:taxAmountTriangulationCurrency
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency and triangulation is used, the amount of that tax in the triangulation currency

label: muc:taxTriangulationCurrency
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency and triangulation is used, the triangulation currency

label: muc:taxTriangulationExchangeRate
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency and triangulation is used, the exchange rate used expressed as national currency divided by triangulation currency

label: muc:taxTriangulationExchangeRateSource
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency and triangulation is used, source of exchange rate - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

label: muc:taxTriangulationExchangeRateType
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency and triangulation is used, type of exchange rate - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

label: muc:taxForeignTriangulationExchangeRate
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency and triangulation is used,  the exchange rate used expressed as foreign currency divided by triangulation currency

label: muc:taxForeignTriangulationExchangeRateSource
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency and triangulation is used, source of exchange rate - for example, Reuters, Bloomberg

label: muc:taxForeignTriangulationExchangeRateType
description: If the tax is in a foreign currency and triangulation is used, type of exchange rate - for example, spot rate, forward contract etc.

label: taf:tickingField
description: Signifies that an item has been cleared, finished, finalized. When checking accounts are called for, the tick or letter showing this was done appears in this field. Can also be used for identifying that the original document against which a payment or DR/CR memo applies has been reconciled.

label: taf:documentRemainingBalance
description: Balance remaining on the document

label: taf:uniqueConsignmentReference
description: Unique Consignment Reference or UCR. An "origin to destination" reference code for international consignments, developed in cooperation with the World Customs Organization and EAN International   EAN.   http://www.wcoomd.org/ie/EN/press/UCR_new_e.pdf

label: taf:originatingDocumentStructure
description: A tool to capture the flow of related documents in the business process. Some needs of end users require a greater history of the documents that are associated with a transaction, especially in the VAT audit area. Contains a repetitive structure of related documents.

label: taf:originatingDocumentType
description: Originating document type  check, debit-memo, credit-memo, finance-charge, invoice, order-customer, order-vendor, payment-other, reminder, tegata, voucher, shipment, receipt, manual-adjustment, other.

label: taf:originatingDocumentNumber
description: Originating document number

label: taf:originatingDocumentDate
description: Originating document date

label: taf:originatingDocumentIdentifierType
description: Originating document identifier type. Enumerated as: C, customer, E, employee, V, vendor, O, other, I, salesperson-internal, X, salesperson-external, N, contractor.

label: taf:originatingDocumentIdentifierCode
description: Originating document identifier code

label: taf:originatingDocumentIdentifierTaxCode
description: Originating document identifier tax code
